# Package (folder) names: prefer plural

When adding or naming **folder segments** that group features (the “package” path under a project, e.g. `Sunday.Application/Clients/...`), use **plural** names for the aggregate/feature: `Clients`, `Brands`, `Tickets`, `WorkSessions`, not `Client` or `Brand`.

## Exceptions

- **Abstractions root**: A folder for shared interfaces/abstractions may be **`Abstract`** (not treated as a plural “domain” name).
- **Use-case subfolders**: Under a plural feature folder, a **verb/action** segment is fine and is **not** plural — e.g. `Clients/Create`, `Tickets/UpdateStatus`, `WorkSessions/Start`. The plural applies to the feature; the inner folder names the operation.

## Examples

```text
✅ Sunday.Application/Clients/Create/CreateClientCommand.cs
✅ Sunday.Core/Abstract/IClientRepository.cs
❌ Sunday.Application/Client/Create/...   (prefer Clients)
```
